cscie97.asn4.housemate.entitlement

Interface IEntitlementVisitor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EntitlementVisitor

    public interface IEntitlementVisitor
    Interface for defining the visit methods that the implementing class must overwrite; follows the Visitor pattern.
    See Also:
    cscie97.asn4.housemate.entitlement.Service, Entitlement, Role, Permission, User

    • Method Detail

      • visitEntitlement

        java.lang.String visitEntitlement(Entitlement entitlement)
        Visits an Entitlement object and returns a string representing its properties. For Role objects, will use the RoleIterator to iterate over all the child Roles and Permissions and include them in the returned string.
        Parameters:
        entitlement - either a Role or Permission to get the properties for
        Returns:
        a string containing the properties of the Entitlement

      • visitPermission

        java.lang.String visitPermission(Permission permission)
        Visits a Permission object and returns a string representing its properties.
        Parameters:
        permission - a Permission to get the properties for
        Returns:
        a string containing the properties of the Permission

      • visitRole

        java.lang.String visitRole(Role role)
        Visits an Role object and returns a string representing its properties. Will use the RoleIterator to iterate over all the child Roles and Permissions and include them in the returned string.
        Parameters:
        role - a Role to get the properties for
        Returns:
        a string containing the properties of the Role

      • visitResource

        java.lang.String visitResource(Resource resource)
        Visits a cscie97.asn4.housemate.entitlement.Service and prints out the properties of the object.
        Parameters:
        resource - the Resource to get the properties for
        Returns:
        a string containing the properties of the Resource

      • visitUser

        java.lang.String visitUser(User user)
        Visits a User and prints out the properties of the object.
        Parameters:
        user - the User to get the properties for
        Returns:
        a string containing the properties of the User

      • visit

        java.lang.String visit(java.lang.Object item)
        Calls the appropriate visit* method based on the object type passed.
        Parameters:
        item - an item that is visitable from the Entitlement Service, such as User, Resource, Role, or Permission
        Returns:
        a string representing the properties of the object
